  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>

    <h3>ARIA Roles</h3>
    <p>The component automatically applies the following ARIA roles:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>role="tablist"</code> on the <code>&lt;tabs-wc&gt;</code> element</li>
      <li><code>role="tab"</code> on each <code>&lt;summary&gt;</code> element</li>
      <li><code>role="tabpanel"</code> on each panel content element</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>ARIA States</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><code>aria-selected</code> indicates the active tab</li>
      <li><code>aria-controls</code> links tabs to their panels</li>
      <li><code>aria-labelledby</code> links panels back to their tabs</li>
      <li><code>tabindex</code> is managed for proper focus order</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Screen Reader Behavior</h3>
    <p>Screen readers will announce the tab interface and allow users to navigate between tabs using the roving tabindex pattern.</p>

